$ halos are more\nextended in high$-z$ LAEs. Our analysis suggests that the Ly$\\alpha$ morphology\naffects the measurement of other observable quantities concerning Ly$\\alpha$\nemission, and some of the conclusions drawn from high redshift LAEs might be\nbiased towards galaxies with specific Ly$\\alpha$ shapes. In particular, faint\nLy$\\alpha$ emitters have larger Ly$\\alpha$ scale lengths and halo fractions.\nThis implies that faint Ly$\\alpha$ emitters are harder to detect at high\nredshift than previously believed.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 4 Oct 2021 18:00:01 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-06-22"}
