ensity of\nmethanol, but cannot reproduce the two different radial profiles observed. We\nconfirm the substantial effect of the environment onto the distribution of\nmethanol in starless cores. We suggest that the clumpy medium generated by\nprotostellar outflows might cause a more efficient penetration of the\ninterstellar radiation field in the molecular cloud and have an impact on the\ndistribution of methanol in starless cores.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 4 Oct 2021 19:14:35 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-12-22"}
